humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states 'METASTATIC CARCINOMA IS PRESENT IN TWO OUT OF TWO LEVEL I LYMPH NODES' which indicates that the patient has metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes (N1) according to Rule 12. However, the report also states 'NUMEROUS FOCI OF METASTATIC CARCINOMA ARE NOTED IN THE AXILLARY SOFT TISSUE, WITH THE LARGEST MEASURING AT LEAST 1.4 CM' which suggests a more advanced stage of lymph node involvement. Therefore, based on Rule 14, the patient's N stage would be N2.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient's pathology report indicates that metastatic carcinoma is present in two out of two level I lymph nodes (2/2) and numerous foci of metastatic carcinoma are noted in the axillary soft tissue, with the largest measuring at least 1.4 cm. This information supports the classification of N2, which refers to cancer that has spread to 1-3 axillary lymph nodes or to the infraclavicular (clavipectoral) lymph nodes.
